For the calculation of average interaction duration per page, the formula is (total page view duration / total pages visited); 
A user's demographics include their age, gender, location, income range, and education level; 
A user's session details include their session code, participant ID, start time, end time, device type, user agent, and session duration; 
Timeouts are events that occur when a user's interaction with a page exceeds a certain time threshold, indicating a potential performance issue.

Top 10 most engaged users refers to the users who have spent the most time interacting with the website within a single session.; 
Cumulative interaction time refers to the running total of interaction time as the user navigates through the website.; 
Navigation refers to the sequence of pages a user visits during a session.
